@Node "Introduction" "Introduction"

    PlaySample is a little utility which makes it possible to play 8SVX
  files.

    This program can only be run under Kickstart v2.04 or higher and
  uses the locale library if it exists. For the moment, only English and
  French are available.

@EndNode

@Node "Starting WB" "Starting from the Workbench"

    Once PlaySample has been started by clicking twice on its icon, it
  opens a file requester asking for a file to play. If the file chosen
  by the user is a 8SVX file, it is then played.

@EndNode

@Node "Starting Shell" "Starting from the Shell"

    When PlaySample is started from the Shell, the syntax is :

      PlaySample [<sample>] [REQ], where :

        <sample> is the name of the 8SVX file,

        REQ tells PlaySample to display a possible error message in a
            requester and not in the Shell window.

    If the <sample> file is actually a 8SVX file, it is played.

@EndNode

@Node "Error messages" "Error messages"

    PlaySample can display the following error messages :

      "Can't open intuition library v37" :

        The intuition library version 37 (or higher) is not available.
        You should use a more recent Kickstart version (at least 2.04).

      "Can't open dos library v37" :

        The dos library version 37 (or higher) is not available. You
        should use a more recent Kickstart version (at least 2.04).

      "Can't open graphics library v37" :

        The graphics library version 37 (or higher) is not available.
        You should use a more recent Kickstart version (at least 2.04).

      "Can't open iffparse library v37" :

        The iffparse library version 37 (or higher) is not available.
        You should use a more recent Workbench version (at least 2.04).

      "Can't open asl library v37" :

        The asl library version 37 (or higher) is not available. You
        should use a more recent Workbench version (at least 2.04).

      "Out of memory" :

        PlaySample needs more memory. Try to free some by closing some
        applications or windows.

      "Can't read file" :

        The chosen file cannot be read. This might be caused by a non-
        existent file name, a disk removed too quickly from the drive, a
        lack of memory, ...

      "The file is not an IFF file" :

        The chosen file is not an IFF file.

      "The file is not an 8SVX file" :

        The chosen file is not an 8SVX file.

      "The file is a musical instrument file" :

        This file is an 8SVX file but it contains the description of a
        musical instrument and not a one-shot sound.

      "Can't get an audio channel" :

        All audio channels are allocated. Try to free one by closing an
        application using one.

@EndNode

